Description:
The round opened for applications on Monday 3rd February. The deadline for applications WAS Friday 28th February 2025. . 

However an update from 5th February states; 
'Thank you for your interest in The Three Guineas Trust's Holiday Activity Programme for 2025. Due to a high level of interest in the Programme, we are closing the grant round for further enquiries/ expressions of interest. We do not want to waste your time applying as the Programme has limited funding resources. If you have already been in touch with our team via email or phone, and meet all the criteria to apply for the scheme, you will receive an application form shortly'

Additional Details:
As shared in our grant making plans earlier this year, the number of applications we receive has increased significantly over the past few years and as a result the proportion of applicants receiving funding has reduced dramatically  ï¿½ in 2024/25 we received almost 1,500 small grant applications. Of these, 100 were successful and received funding. This has prompted a review of our small grants programme, so that we can ensure our processes are as simple as possible for applicants and our funding delivers maximum impact to communities across the UK and beyond.What we have done

We asked more than 1,200 applicants for their views;
Considered insights from across the wider grant making sector;
Reviewed our grant application form and process.
Following a comprehensive review of the valuable feedback, the Fund has refined its small grants programme plans for 25/26 to improve the application process and ensure support reaches those small organisations we aim to fund.
